{{fq
|text = You ever heard of a [[horse]] being called "as healthy as a [[half-orc|half orc]]?" No, I didn't think so. They keep just fine, and so would you.
|source = [[Groncaner]]
}}
Unlike some other taverns, patrons of the Crooked Crane had to serve themselves. There was essentially no table service at all. The lodging was not fancy, and only really catered to those who were poor or desperate. The owner, Groncaner, offered weary wayfarers blankets to sleep in the tavern for only 1 [[gold piece]].

The bar only served [[ale]] and [[mead]]. Around [[1368 DR]], the ale menu consisted of: [[Bitter Black]], [[Iriaeboran North Brew]], [[Luiren's Best]], and [[Tanagyr's Stout]].
